# Reuse shared code before duplicating it

- **Search first** for an existing helper, hook, service, or type before writing one.
- **Extract on the third copy**—two snippets can coincide; three is a signal.
- **Pick the right home**: an existing module, or `*/shared/`, `*/lib/`, `*/utils/`. Never bury shared code inside an unrelated feature.
- **Narrow surface**: export a small, well-named function or type—not a "helpers" grab-bag.
- **Compose** existing functions/components/hooks; pass parameters instead of forking near-duplicates.
- **Avoid premature abstraction**: if cases will likely diverge, keep them separate; revisit at the third caller.
- **Update call sites** when you extract—don't leave stale copies that drift.

```typescript
// ❌ same logic copy-pasted
function totalA(items: Item[]) { return items.reduce((s, i) => s + i.priceCents, 0); }
function totalB(rows: Item[])  { return rows.reduce((s, r) => s + r.priceCents, 0); }

// ✅ one shared function reused everywhere
export function sumPriceCents(items: readonly Item[]): number {
  return items.reduce((sum, item) => sum + item.priceCents, 0);
}
```
